					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lt-flops" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735419); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735419&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250794" alt="Lt Flops" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735419)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lt-flops" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735419); return false;" >Lt Flops</a></span> <span class="odate time_1567362436 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Sep 2019 18:27</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4347105">
									

<p>There are some pretty funny parts to this. A major issue I have, though, is that there are <em>so many</em> comedic angles involved. Almost every single line is a separate joke, often with little consistency between one another, each making <em>some</em> attempt to garner entertainment or laughter from the reader. To me, a lot of the joke set-ups fall flat, turning this into a slog to get through. The various zany references to other articles on the site seem completely random. I also don't see the connection between the Wendy's references, the break-ups, and the gross-out moments.</p>
<p>I can see there was a lot of effort put into this, and I would suggest just sticking to one theme instead of attempting so many disparate ones.</p>

							</div>

